---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Kai Ning's technical blog: Kubernetes, GitOps, AI agents, and infrastructure engineering."
>
  <section class="page-intro">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>Why this blog exists</h1>
    <p>
      I wanted a technical home base that feels closer to field notes than to a
      polished marketing page. The main lens is Kubernetes. The secondary lens
      is AI and agent infrastructure. The common thread is production reality.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section-grid">
    <article class="feature-card">
      <h2>What shows up here</h2>
      <p>
        Cluster debugging, deployment safety, GitOps review habits,
        observability patterns, runtime behavior, and the operational work
        behind reliable systems.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="feature-card">
      <h2>How the writing is shaped</h2>
      <p>
        The bias is toward practical defaults, explicit tradeoffs, and examples
        that can survive contact with real environments without too much
        ceremony.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="feature-card">
      <h2>What this rebuild changed</h2>
      <p>
        This repository now runs on Astro with a lightweight content model and
        a GitHub Pages workflow intended to stay maintainable as the blog grows.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="page-intro page-intro--compact">
    <p class="eyebrow">Working principles</p>
    <h2>What I want each post to do</h2>
    <ul class="focus-list">
      <li>Answer a real operational question</li>
      <li>Show the default I would start with</li>
      <li>Be specific enough to reuse, not just admire</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
